qas.question: Where did Eisenhower work during his brother's first year of college?
What was Eisenhower's job title during the first year his brother went to college?
In what year did Eisenhower matriculate to West Point?

context: Edgar took the first turn at school, and Dwight was employed as a <a1_0>night supervisor<a1_0/> at the <a0_0>Belle Springs Creamery<a0_0/>. Edgar asked for a second year, Dwight consented and worked for a second year. At that time, a friend "Swede" Hazlet was applying to the Naval Academy and urged Dwight to apply to the school, since no tuition was required. Eisenhower requested consideration for either Annapolis or West Point with his U.S. Senator, <a2_0>Joseph L. Bristow<a2_0/>. Though Eisenhower was among the winners of the entrance-exam competition, he was <a3_0>beyond the age limit<a3_0/> for the Naval Academy. He then accepted an appointment to West Point in <a4_0>1911<a4_0/>.
